\begintext
================================================================================
MKSPK Setup File Template - Create Satellite Ephemeris from TLE
================================================================================

This file tells mkspk how to create an SPK (ephemeris) file from Two-Line
Element (TLE) data. The SPK file contains satellite position over time.

HOW TO USE:
1. Copy this file and rename it for your satellite (e.g., mysat_ephemeris.setup)
2. Fill in the values below (see comments for guidance)
3. Run: create_ephemeris_from_tle("your_setup.setup", output_dir)

REQUIRED FILES:
- A TLE file containing orbital elements for your satellite
- A leapseconds kernel (.tls file) - use the one in data/spice_kernels/generic/lsk/
- A planetary constants kernel (.ker or .tpc) - use the one in data/spice_kernels/generic/pck/

================================================================================
\begindata

INPUT_DATA_TYPE   = 'TL_ELEMENTS'
OUTPUT_SPK_TYPE   = 10

\begintext
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
SATELLITE IDENTIFIERS
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
TLE_INPUT_OBJ_ID: The NORAD catalog number from your TLE file (5-digit number)
TLE_SPK_OBJ_ID:   The SPICE ID for your satellite (negative number, e.g., -126824)
                  Convention: Use negative numbers for spacecraft
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
\begindata

TLE_INPUT_OBJ_ID  = 26824
TLE_SPK_OBJ_ID    = -126824

\begintext
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
REFERENCE FRAME AND CENTER
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
CENTER_ID:      399 = Earth (satellites orbit around Earth)
REF_FRAME_NAME: J2000 is the standard inertial reference frame
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
\begindata

CENTER_ID         = 399
REF_FRAME_NAME    = 'J2000'

\begintext
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
INPUT/OUTPUT FILES (paths relative to where you run the command)
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
LEAPSECONDS_FILE: Path to leap seconds kernel
INPUT_DATA_FILE:  Path to your TLE file
OUTPUT_SPK_FILE:  Where to write the output ephemeris
PCK_FILE:         Path to planetary constants kernel (for Earth parameters)
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
\begindata

LEAPSECONDS_FILE  = 'data/spice_kernels/generic/lsk/naif0012.tls.pc'
INPUT_DATA_FILE   = 'data/tle/your_satellite.tle'
OUTPUT_SPK_FILE   = 'output/your_satellite.bsp'
PCK_FILE          = 'data/spice_kernels/generic/pck/geophysical.ker'

\begintext
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
TIME WINDOW
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
START_TIME / STOP_TIME: The time range for which to generate ephemeris
                        Format: 'YYYY MON DD' (e.g., '2020 JAN 01')
                        Must be within the validity range of your TLE data
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
\begindata

START_TIME        = '2020 JAN 01'
STOP_TIME         = '2025 JAN 01'

\begintext
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
OPTIONAL SETTINGS
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
PRODUCER_ID:      Your name/organization (appears in kernel metadata)
APPEND_TO_OUTPUT: 'YES' to append to existing file, 'NO' to overwrite
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
\begindata

PRODUCER_ID       = 'LCAS User'
APPEND_TO_OUTPUT  = 'NO'

